cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for 3D shape parameterization and completion using machine learning techniques. The method involves encoding 3D surface detail on local patches and learning a patch dictionary to identify principal surface features of the shape. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves novel methods for dictionary learning and patch reconstruction, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the patch dictionary towards various applications in 3D shape inpainting, denoising, and compression, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
